<mainText attr1="Piloting Overview:"/>
<mainText attr1="Void Destroyer's flight mechanics has been inspired by classic space sims where speed settings exist. There is no limit that your ship can travel forwards/backwards or in other directions - this can be controlled via manual thrusts. Unlike classic space sims Void Destroyer features Newtonian flight, meaning that unless acted upon your ship will travel in the direction of its momentum. For example - while moving you can rotate your ship without impacting its movement vector. To simplify piloting you can set a speed (see cruise speed, increase/decrease speed) and your ship will automatically thrust to reach that setting (enabled by default). You can disable ship's automatic thrusts and thus manually control your velocity in 3D space (see smart thrust). This is useful for avoiding obstacles, doing strafing runs and avoiding enemy fire."/>
<mainText attr1=" "/>
<mainText attr1="To get truly good at space combat, you'll need to master speed settings, manual thrusts, afterburner and turning on/off smart thrust."/>
<mainText attr1=" "/>
<mainText attr1="For more strategy oriented players - you can toggle crew control to let your ship's crew take over."/>
